[4] UK (Wales)
Date: Mon 7 Oct 2013
Source: Wales online [abbreviated & edited]
http://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/health/measles-health-officials-urge-vaccination-6151898


Two doses of MMR are needed to provide the maximum 99 percent protection against measles, and Public Health Wales are aware of more than 30 000 children in the 10-18 age group who remain unvaccinated in Wales. Health officials are urging parents to make sure their children are vaccinated against measles after being notified of 3 more cases of the virus. Public Health Wales said there are now 3 cases associated with Cwmtawe School, Neath Port Talbot, one of which has been laboratory confirmed. Another 2 probable cases have been identified in children in Ysgol Y Cribarth, Powys who are connected to the confirmed case at Cwmtawe School. Tomorrow [8 Oct 2013], more than 200 children at Cwmtawe School will be offered the vaccination. Of 1260 pupils at the school, 62 are recorded as having received no doses of the MMR vaccine, and 142 have received only one dose. As the number of unvaccinated children at Ysgol Y Cribarth is so small, Powys Teaching Health Board is making arrangements for susceptible children to be immunised individually.

[Byline: Julia McWatt]

