[5] Pakistan (Punjab)
Date: Thu 10 Oct 2013
Source: Geo TV News Pakistan [edited]
http://www.geo.tv/article-121728-LHC-annoyed-over-non-submission-of-inquiry-report-in-measles-case


Lahore High Court (LHC) on Wednesday [9 Oct 2013] lashed out [at] the Punjab government for its continued failure in submitting an inquiry report prepared by a 3-member committee headed by Dr Zafar Iqbal, Principal Sheikh Zayed Hospital, into the alleged failure of the government to control the recent outbreak of measles, Geo News reported.

While hearing the measles case here, the court, expressing its extreme displeasure over non-submission of the measles inquiry report, observed that people were dying of measles while the Punjab Chief Minister, untouched by the tragedy, [is] sitting with the report.

The Additional Advocate General told the court that the report was lying with the Chief Minister, and Justice Khalid Mahmood observed that the people were dying and the Chief Minster was unmoved and was sitting with the report. He further said that the CM takes his salary from the national exchequer, and the welfare of the nation was his prime duty.

Justice Khalid Mahmood ordered the submission of the inquiry report within 3 days and later adjourned the hearing of the case until 14 Oct 2013.

